20.title: Course Overview
20.content: CIS 376 Web Development introduces students to front-end web development technologies and practices. Students will learn HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, and modern development workflows while building professional-quality web applications. Learning Objectives . | Master HTML5 semantic markup and accessibility principles | Create responsive layouts using CSS3 and Bootstrap framework | Implement interactive functionality with JavaScript and DOM manipulation | Develop professional development workflows using Git and GitHub | Deploy static websites using GitHub Pages | Apply web development best practices and industry standards | .
